BUG: Cleanup uses msgResult.changes but Cloudflare sql.exec() returns a cursor with rowsRead/rowsWritten, NOT changes property. Cleanup metrics are wrong/misleading.

Current (wrong):
  const msgResult = this.sql.exec('DELETE ...');
  console.log(msgResult.changes);  // undefined

Fixed:
  const cursor = this.sql.exec('DELETE ...', oneDayAgo);
  console.log(cursor.rowsWritten);

Also: cleanup should run via scheduled events/DO alarms, not manual /cleanup calls.

Files: ccr-worker/src/router-do.js (handleCleanup)
Ref: ChatGPT code review 2026-01-22, Cloudflare SQLite docs

BUG: When machine reconnects before old socket emits 'close', the old socket's close handler deletes the NEW socket from the map. Result: machine appears offline despite being connected.

Current (buggy):
  this.machines.set(machineId, server);
  server.addEventListener('close', () => {
    this.machines.delete(machineId);  // Deletes new socket\!
  });

Fixed:
  server.addEventListener('close', () => {
    if (this.machines.get(machineId) === server) {
      this.machines.delete(machineId);
    }
  });

Also consider proactively closing old socket when new one arrives.

Files: ccr-worker/src/router-do.js (handleWebSocket, around line 150)
